\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. C. arundinacea} (L.) Roth,{\i  Tent. Fl. Germ.}{\b  2}({\b 1}): 89 (1789). Caespitose, with short rhizomes; stems 60-150 cm, erect, rather stout, with 2-3 nodes, smooth. Leaves up to 50 cm × 4-12 mm, flat, hairy at junction of lamina and sheath, the upper surface scabrid, with widely spaced veins; ligule 2-4 mm, obtuse or truncate. Panicle 10-25 × up to 5 cm, often rather dense; branches scabrid or weakly aculeolate. Spikelets 4-6 mm, light brown to purplish. Glumes subequal, lanceolate, scabridulous. Lemma 2-fid at apex; awn bent and twisted, about twice as long as and arising from near base of lemma. Callus-hairs not more than ½ as long as lemma. 2n = 28+0-2B.{\i  Open woods and marshes. Most of Europe except the islands, the extreme north and much of the south-west.} Au Be Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Gr He Hs Hu It Ju Lu No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C,W, E) Su.
