\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. C. fasciculatus} (Link) Hayek,{\i  Prodr. Fl. Penins. Balcan. }{\b 3}: 335 (1933). Stems up to 20 cm, slender, ascending. Leaves up to 1 mm wide; ligule up to 5 mm, acute. Panicle 0·5-12 cm. Spikelets c. 3 mm (excl. awn), often in groups of 2-3; pedicels short, stout. Glumes lanceolate-subulate, scabrid; awn 1-3 times as long as glume. Lemma somewhat shorter than the glumes. 2n = 14. {\i Sandy places. Mediterranean region, Portugal.} Hs It Ju Lu.
